Our circle is open to bringing on 1 (or 2 if new members only come in pairs) new member to our Circle if we can find someone(s) who fits at least some of the following criteria (in order of importance):
 1. Artistic (e.g. someone whose primary work is as a creative)
 2. A parent of older children (e.g. teen) and/or children with disabilities
 3. A woman of color
 
 We recognize we are looking for a bit of a unicorn, so if this person is not out there, we are also fine staying with our current circle formation. 
 
 While we are primarily a virtual circle, all members have ties to New York and we try to meet in person 1-2 times per year. column52: I know that GSB Women's Circles is going to give me something very needed but missing in my life right now. I have been a ferociously intense overachiever since grade school and not only career-obsessed but in a hurry to rack up achievements. I'm in this weird place now where I feel like I'm losing some of that drive and it's for a number of reasons - I've been away from it for a year, I've had some health challenges post-pregnancy that knocked me off my game, I'm now a mother, I needed this respite after after a difficult 3-year IVF process, and i just needed respite from the incredibly intense nonstop academic and career journey I've been on. I know that I cannot go back to the same level of intensity I was prior to this pregnancy, for my own sanity and health, and even for the health of my marriage and my son. I also recognize this is a unique opportunity for me to actually find something I am passionate about in ways that exceed "I'm good at this" and "this is what financial and career success means". And I feel like talking to other women who I can relate to in any of these capacities will help me make sense of a lot of what's floating around in my head. So I'm excited about the opportunity to connect with other women that I can relate to and can relate to me to uplift other women and share things that can be helpful to them where possible, and to feel supported overall.
